<p valign="top">SEND(2) avr-Xinu SEND(2)</p>

<p style="margin-top: 1em" valign="top"><b>NAME</b></p>

<p style="margin-left:8%;">send &minus; send a (one-word)
message to a process</p>


<p style="margin-top: 1em" valign="top"><b>SYNOPSIS</b></p>

<p style="margin-left:8%;"><i>int send(pid, msg) <br>
int pid; <br>
int msg;</i></p>


<p style="margin-top: 1em" valign="top"><b>DESCRIPTION</b></p>

<p style="margin-left:8%;"><i>Send</i> sends the one-word
message <i>msg</i> to the process with id <i>pid.</i> A
process may have at most one outstanding message that has
not been received.</p>

<p style="margin-left:8%; margin-top: 1em"><i>Send</i>
returns SYSERR if <i>pid</i> is invalid or if the process
already has a message waiting that has not been received.
Otherwise, it sends the message and returns OK.</p>

<p style="margin-top: 1em" valign="top"><b>SEE ALSO</b></p>

<p style="margin-left:8%;">receive(2), sendf(2),
preceive(2), psend(2)</p>

<p style="margin-left:8%; margin-top: 1em">XINU V7
